<TITLE> Khaleda charged with embezzlement </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 5 (bdnews24.com)The Anticorruption Commission has pressed charges in the court against opposition BNP chief Khaleda Zia, elder son Tarique Rahman and four others in the Zia Orphanage Trust embezzlement case. Khaleda, a two-time former prime minister, and the others face charges of embezzling more than Tk 2 crore by throwing up the Trust that allegedly exists only on paper. ACC deputy assistant director Harun-ur-Rashid filed the charge sheet to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka. Harun, the investigating officer, dropped charges against Syed Ahmed and Gias Uddin Ahmed in the case had filed against seven people with Ramna Police Station on July 3, 2008. The four other defendants in the case are former BNP MP Kazi Salimul Haque, Sharfuddin Ahmed and Mominur Rahman, a nephew of Khaleda, and Kamal Uddin Siddiqui, former principal secretary at the prime minister's office. Mominur Rahman and Sharfuddin Ahmed were on the run and the the rest have been freed on bail, he said. Harun also said a total of 36 people have been made state witnesses to the case. The Supreme Court on Aug 2 this year upheld Khaleda's bail in the case that the High Court granted her on Aug 26, 2008. bdnew
